The memorandum is a directive from President Joseph R. Biden Jr. to the Secretary of Homeland Security and the Administrator of the Federal Emergency Management Agency (FEMA). The memorandum states that the policy of the administration is to combat and respond to the COVID-19 pandemic with the full capacity and capability of the federal government. It directs FEMA to provide a 100 percent federal cost share for all work eligible for assistance under Public Assistance Category B, which includes emergency protective measures related to COVID-19. The memorandum also includes general provisions, stating that it does not impair the authority of executive departments or agencies, and that it is subject to applicable law and the availability of appropriations. The Administrator of FEMA is authorized and directed to publish the memorandum in the Federal Register.